   <refnamediv>
       <refname>bintodec </refname>
               <refpurpose>During each BMA step, convert "base 2" models codification into bits </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>vsave = bintodec(binsave,nvar)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> binsave </term> =    vector of numbered different visited models in binary codes</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> nvar </term> =    # of exogenous variable</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term>  vsave </term> =    matrix of ones (indication that a variable has been selected) and zeros (otherwise)</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Function used for bayesian model averaging codes. It converts "base 2" models codification into bits.
memory).
 
